pecies":"krokorok","gen":"generation-v","leg":false,"myth":false,"baby":false,"eggs":["ground"],"flavor":[{"version":"black","text":"They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms."},{"version":"white","text":"The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings even in darkness."},{"version":"black-2","text":"Protected by thin membranes, their eyes can see even in the dead of night. They live in groups of a few individuals."},{"version":"white-2","text":"Protected by thin membranes, their eyes can see even in the dead of night. They live in groups of a few individuals."},{"version":"x","text":"They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms."},{"version":"y","text":"The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings even in darkness."},{"version":"omega-ruby","text":"They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms."},{"version":"alpha-sapphire","text":"The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings even in darkness."},{"version":"sun","text":"They move in groups of a few individuals. A female is often the leader of the group, and the males will gather food."},{"version":"moon","text":"Thanks to the special membrane covering its eyes, it can see its surroundings clearly, even in the middle of the night."},{"version":"ultra-sun","text":"Krokorok really hates it when its body gets cold. On nights when the temperature drops, it digs deep into the desert sands."},{"version":"ultra-moon","text":"It buries some of its prey in the sand to use as emergency meals when its hunts are unsuccessful."},{"version":"sword","text":"Krokorok has specialized eyes that enable it to see in the dark. This ability lets Krokorok hunt in the dead of night without getting lost."},{"version":"shiel